description.narrative: To reduce the acceptance of violence against children, UNICEF launched the first Girls' Empowerment Initiative marking a clear political statement to tackle the root causes of harmful practices and 5 multimedia campaigns promoting positive parenting and protection of children from abuses extensively supported by strategic partnerships with the private sector. Furthermore, an interactive parenting program promoting positive gender socialization has been conceived. As a result, 3.3 million viewers have been engaged on line and 3.3 million in face to face related activities with an improved awareness in terms of behaviors protecting children from abuses and promoting their full potential. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/02/2020
